 Similarly for pair-creation: pair-creation is the rending-apart of the
 space-time manifold, with two half-tears propagrating along.
 Here, the model resembles the standard conceptual model of the Dirac sea:
 each side provides what the other is missing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conservation of angular momentum.
 Presumably, the equations for the merger of 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi$
\end_inset

-holes and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\psi}$
\end_inset

-holes do not require the violation of angular momentum conservation.
 If they do, then there is trouble, as normally, a pair of photons are required
 for conservation of angular momentum.
 It would be weird and interesting if this model somehow forced the use
 of an auxilliary 
\begin_inset Formula $U\left(1\right)$
\end_inset

-bundle to restore angular momentum.
 If this happened to be required, then it would be interesting, as it might
 explain why photons don't experience proper time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conservation of energy.
 There are no overt, explicit masses in the proposed model, and so presumably
 a conservation of momentum does not offer any challanges.
 Maybe.
 The model proposes that the holes are accompanied by closed spinor-forms,
 i.e.
 obey a differential equation 
\begin_inset Formula $d\psi=0$
\end_inset

